So I Made a CR Twitter

Hey everyone!! So I finally caved and made myself a CR twitter so I could post about D&D, CR, and widofjord in peace without bothering my space friends. My handle is @cut_palms so feel free to join me if you’re interested.

summary: Crack ship: Kima and Beau
question: Crack ship: Kima and Beau
answer:
• Both are super into fighting shit
  • stronger then people think they are
  • real fucking angry at things
  • do more physical fighting then magic
  • really want to punch a dragon
  • both part of some type of order of people
  • kinda adopted and taken under the wing of an older master
  • they’d appreciate each others power
  • Probably both love Allura a whole lot
  • headstrong
  • loyal as all hell

Their kind of perfect for each other in a way almost, though the huge age cap with how long Kima has been retired from adventuring is an issue. She and Allura have a good married life going on, and Beau doesn’t seem the commitment type in the long run unfortunately. Kima is looking for a relationship, not a one night stand or anything.

body:
fjord-mustang mentioned you in a post “You know, I read a couple times that Vox Machina is more morally…”
…bits over being defecated. @ hostilemakeover Yeah, this is all…

I know Liev’Tel popped the fossil off her forehead, but I sincerely hope they didn’t jam anything, like… in her skull. The whole thing made me cringe, but I don’t love the players any less - I just love the characters who did not partake in the shannangins a little more.
